<br>
Following Bertoxxulous on the land of<br>
Antonica is kind of like being an Iksar.<br>
The NPC's glower at you dubiously or worse,<br>
and as for the PC's--they're all Neutral or Good.<br>
<br>
I need some RP allies and maybe an Evil-<br>
aligned &quot;family.&quot;  FV is making me kind of<br>
queasy because Toxxy is not well-accepted<br>
among many players in Norrath, and those that<br>
do accept Him only do so VERY minimally.<br>
<br>
Any takers want a Toxxy Cleric? *grin*<br>
<br>
Yours,<br>
Atrilinea<br>
11th Acolyte of Virulence <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/udeffhead01.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Deffhead01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/7/01 7:08:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm42.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Minions of Bertoxxulous, let us unite!</span><hr size=1> Greetings Atrilinea!<br>
<br>
I have had the exact same experience on Firiona Vie. I am sort of lonely as well, since I do not assosiate with elves or any other goodie two-shoe, which cuts out the majority in FV. Next is this followers of Innoruuk, I could accept working with them to reach a common goal, but it would only ever be a very uneasy alliance. And add to that the fact that they do not understand me, at all. <br>
So actually I have only grouped a little bit back in the Steamfront Mountains, and I must admit that I am bored of travelling alone all the time. <br>
Then I met this guild of gnomes following our Lord the Plaguebringer, and I joined their organization. But it seems that when I travel Norrath, there are very few, if any, of them around, so now I am back to square one.<br>
<br>
So basicly, what I am saying is, that I will be happy to travel with and get to know any minion of Bertoxxulous, regardless of race and prowess.<br>
<br>
<br>
I am currently searching the continent of Kunark for some arcane lore on an ancient artifact imbued with the powers of the Plaguebringer. But, if needs be, I'd can postpone the search and come meet you somewhere on Antonica...<br>
Let me know your whereabouts, then I will come and meet you.<br>
<br>
<br>
(By the way, if there are any other Bertoxxulous followers out there, be sure to let us know! Together we grow stronger.) <p><b>Milton Finkelstein</b><br>
Gnomish Bonecrafter<br>
Firiona Vie server</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukentassolgaard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kentas Solgaard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/7/01 9:34:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm42.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Looking for a RP family, or at least allies! :-)</span><hr size=1> Although I still find the followers of Bertoxxulous rather incompetent for that 'stunt' they pulled out on the Karanas and its eventual failure, they did at least know how to teach meditation.<br>
